7 of the court and the consent of the prosecuting attorney. A defendant
8 who pleads not guilty to the charge of a capital offense must be tried
9 by jury.
10 2. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 1, in a justice
11 court, a case must be tried by jury only if the defendant so demands
12 in writing not less than 30 days before trial. [Except as otherwise
13 provided in NRS 4.390 and 4.400, if a case is tried by jury, a
14 reporter must be present who is a certified court reporter and shall
15 report the trial.]
16 3. Any proceeding before a jury in justice court may be
17 recorded using sound recording equipment in accordance with
18 NRS 4.390 and 4.400.
